+# v0 Edge Cases
+
+## 1) API shape drift
+v0 UI and CLI surfaces change. Prefer current commands shown in docs or chat UI outputs. Avoid relying on stale snippets.
+
+## 2) Large import shock
+Importing too many files at once can hide regressions.
+
+- Do incremental imports
+- Validate `package.json`, aliases, and path resolution after each batch
+
+## 3) Next.js module boundaries
+Generated UI might mix server/client concerns.
+
+- Ensure client-only logic is in files with `'use client'`
+- Keep API routes and server components separated
+
+## 4) Design token mismatch
+Generated style can use inconsistent tokens if the project baseline differs.
+
+- Normalize to `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, spacing scale, and radius conventions
+- Verify dark mode state with Theme provider where applicable
+
+## 5) Deploy/branch surprises
+When GitHub-connected flows are enabled, preview and production behavior should be validated manually from the generated links and deployment logs.
+
+## 6) Secret handling
+Do not paste secrets in chat prompts. Always pass via env and CI variables.
+
